<tr><td><strong>Business</strong></td><td>$40/mo</td><td>Unlimited transcription, team collaboration, brand kits, custom export presets</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p>The Hobbyist plan at $24/month is the sweet spot for individual creators and freelancers. The 10 hours of transcription per month covers most podcast episodes, YouTube videos, and tutorial series. Studio Sound and the lack of watermarks make it feel like a fully professional tool. The Business plan at $40/month is ideal for teams producing large volumes of content, with unlimited transcription and collaboration features that scale across multiple projects and contributors.</p>

<h2>Pros and Cons</h2>

<h3>What We Loved ✅</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Edit video like a Word doc</strong> — Transcript-first editing is incredibly intuitive and saves hours per project</li>
  <li><strong>Studio Sound is magical</strong> — AI audio cleanup transforms poor recordings into studio-quality audio</li>
  <li><strong>Overdub voice cloning</strong> — Correct mistakes and add new lines without re-recording</li>
  <li><strong>Filler word removal</strong> — One-click removal of ums, uhs, and silences across the entire project</li>
  <li><strong>Collaborative editing</strong> — Real-time multi-user editing with comments and version history</li>
  <li><strong>Direct publishing</strong> — Export and publish to YouTube, Vimeo, and social platforms without leaving the app</li>
  <li><strong>Screen recording + transcription</strong> — Record, transcribe, and edit tutorials in one seamless workflow</li>
</ul>

<h3>What Could Be Better ❌</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Resource-intensive on older hardware</strong> — Real-time transcription and AI processing can slow down older computers</li>
  <li><strong>Limited visual effects</strong> — Not suitable for complex animations, motion graphics, or cinematic color grading</li>
  <li><strong>Free tier is very restrictive</strong> — 1 hour of transcription per month with watermarked export barely qualifies as a trial</li>
  <li><strong>AI features depend on audio quality</strong> — Overdub and Studio Sound degrade noticeably with very poor source audio</li>
  <li><strong>No mobile editor</strong> — Desktop-only; no mobile app for on-the-go editing or review</li>
  <li><strong>Export speed varies</strong> — Longer projects with multiple effects can take significant time to render</li>
</ul>

<h2>Descript vs Competitors</h2>

